{"date": 0, "url": 0, "text": "January 2  \u2013 President Obama signs the  James Zadroga 9/11 Health and Compensation Act of 2010 ,  H.R. 847 , into law at his vacation rental house,  Plantation Estate , in  Hawaii . [1]"}
{"date": 1, "url": 1, "text": "January 4  \u2013 President Obama signs 35  acts  into law including the Government Performance and Results Modernization Act of 2010 and the FDA  Food Safety Modernization Act . [2]"}
{"date": 2, "url": 2, "text": "January 10  \u2013 President Obama leads a national  moment of silence  for the victims of the  2011 Tucson shooting . [3]  French President  Nicolas Sarkozy  meets with President Obama at the  White House  in anticipation of  France 's hosting of the  G8  and  G20  summits. [4]"}
{"date": 3, "url": 3, "text": "January 12  \u2013 President Obama has a morning meeting with Prime Minister  Saad Hariri  of  Lebanon . [5]  Afterward, the President and  First Lady   Michelle Obama  travel to  Tucson, Arizona , where they visit  Representative   Gabrielle Giffords  and other survivors of the  recent shooting ; later, the President  delivers remarks  at a memorial service for the six victims of the shooting. [6]"}
{"date": 4, "url": 4, "text": "January 19  \u2013 President and Mrs. Obama welcome Chinese President  Hu Jintao  to the White House for a  state visit . [7]"}
{"date": 5, "url": 5, "text": "January 21  \u2013 President Obama announces that  Paul Volcker  will be stepping down as an adviser to the Economic Recovery Advisory Board. [8]"}
{"date": 6, "url": 6, "text": "January 25  \u2013 President Obama delivers his  State of the Union Address  to a  joint session of Congress . [9]"}
{"date": 7, "url": 7, "text": "February 1  \u2013 President Obama delivers remarks on the  protests in Egypt . [10]"}
{"date": 8, "url": 8, "text": "February 2  \u2013 President Obama signs the instrument of  ratification  for  New START , a nuclear arms reduction treaty between the United States and the Russian Federation. [11]"}
{"date": 9, "url": 9, "text": "February 3  \u2013 President Obama speaks at the  National Prayer Breakfast . [12]  The President visits  Penn State University  to promote his \"Better Buildings\" energy conservation initiative. [13]"}
{"date": 10, "url": 10, "text": "February 7  \u2013 The President speaks at a meeting of the  United States Chamber of Commerce  at  the organization's headquarters  near the White House. [14]"}
{"date": 11, "url": 11, "text": "February 10  \u2013 President Obama travels to  Northern Michigan University  to promote the school's  WiMAX  system. [15]"}
{"date": 12, "url": 12, "text": "February 11  \u2013 President Obama speaks about the  revolution in Egypt  following the resignation of Egyptian President  Hosni Mubarak . [16]   Jay Carney  replaces  Robert Gibbs  as  White House Press Secretary . [17]"}
{"date": 13, "url": 13, "text": "February 14  \u2013 The President unveils his  spending request for the 2012 federal budget . [18]  President Obama visits  Parkville Middle School and Center of Technology  in  Baltimore County, Maryland , to highlight educational priorities in his proposed 2012 budget. [19]"}
{"date": 14, "url": 14, "text": "February 15  \u2013 President Obama presents the  Presidential Medal of Freedom  to  fifteen people  in a ceremony at the White House. [20]"}
{"date": 15, "url": 15, "text": "February 17  \u2013 President Obama and the  CEOs  of major technology companies\u2014including  Carol Bartz ,  John Chambers ,  Dick Costolo ,  Larry Ellison ,  Reed Hastings ,  Steve Jobs ,  Art Levinson ,  Eric Schmidt ,  Steve Westly ,  Mark Zuckerberg , and  Stanford University  president  John L. Hennessy \u2014meet at the home of  John Doerr  to discuss the President's innovation initiatives. [21] [22]"}
{"date": 16, "url": 16, "text": "February 22  \u2013 The President speaks at the Winning the Future Forum on Small Business at  Cleveland State University . [23] [24]"}
{"date": 17, "url": 17, "text": "February 23  \u2013 President Obama visits with wounded service members and their families at the  National Naval Medical Center  and awards six  Purple Heart  medals. [25]  President Obama delivers a televised statement on the  situation in Libya . [26]"}
{"date": 18, "url": 18, "text": "February 27  \u2013 The 2011 Governors' Dinner is hosted by President Obama in the  State Dining Room  of the White House. [27]  The President makes an appearance in a pre-recorded clip shown during the  83rd Academy Awards  ceremony. [27]"}
{"date": 19, "url": 19, "text": "March 1  \u2013 President Obama meets with the  Conference of Presidents of Major American Jewish Organizations  in the State Dining Room of the White House. [28]"}
{"date": 20, "url": 20, "text": "March 2  \u2013 President Obama presents the  National Medal of Arts  and the  National Humanities Medal  to awardees in a ceremony at the White House. [29]  The President signs a  short-term budget extension bill  to fund the federal government through March 18. [30]"}
{"date": 21, "url": 21, "text": "March 3  \u2013 President Obama holds meetings and a press conference with President  Felipe Calder\u00f3n  of Mexico. [31]"}
{"date": 22, "url": 22, "text": "March 7  \u2013 President Obama holds meetings and a press conference with Prime Minister  Julia Gillard  of Australia. [32]"}
{"date": 23, "url": 23, "text": "March 8  \u2013 The President ends his two-year ban on military trials for detainees held at  Guantanamo Bay  with Executive Order 13567. [33]"}
{"date": 24, "url": 24, "text": "March 10  \u2013 The President and First Lady host the first Conference on  Bullying  Prevention at the White House. [34]"}
{"date": 25, "url": 25, "text": "March 19  \u2013 President Obama orders military air strikes against  Muammar Gaddafi 's forces in  Libya . Shortly afterward, the President travels to  Rio de Janeiro ,  Brazil  to meet with President  Dilma Rousseff . [35]"}
{"date": 26, "url": 26, "text": "March 21  \u2013 The First Family arrives in  Santiago ,  Chile . [36]"}
{"date": 27, "url": 27, "text": "March 28  \u2013 President Obama delivers a speech at the  National Defense University  explaining his rationale for ordering United States  military intervention in Libya . [37]"}
{"date": 28, "url": 28, "text": "March 30  \u2013 President Obama discusses domestic energy policy and hybrid vehicles at  Georgetown University . [38]"}
{"date": 29, "url": 29, "text": "April 4  \u2013 President Obama announces his  bid for re-election . [39]"}
{"date": 30, "url": 30, "text": "April 5  \u2013 The President meets with  congressional  leaders to discuss the  ongoing federal budget debate ; later in the day, President Obama meets with Israeli President  Shimon Peres . [40]"}
{"date": 31, "url": 31, "text": "April 6  \u2013 After trips to  Philadelphia  and  New York City  earlier in the day, the President calls an evening meeting with  Speaker of the House   John Boehner  and  Senate Majority Leader   Harry Reid  to discuss the ongoing federal budget debate. [41] [42]"}
{"date": 32, "url": 32, "text": "April 27  \u2013 The White House releases a copy of President Obama's \"long-form\"  birth certificate . [43]"}
{"date": 33, "url": 33, "text": "April 29  \u2013 The President meets with participants of the 1968  Memphis Sanitation Strike  at the White House; travels to  Alabama  to view damage from the  recent tornado outbreak  and meet with  Governor   Robert J. Bentley ; and delivers the  commencement address  at  Miami Dade College . [44]"}
{"date": 34, "url": 34, "text": "April 30  \u2013 President Obama attends the annual  White House Correspondents' Association Dinner . [45]"}
{"date": 35, "url": 35, "text": "May 2  \u2013 President Obama announces that  Osama bin Laden  has been  killed . [46]"}
{"date": 36, "url": 36, "text": "May 5  \u2013 The President lays a wreath at \" Ground Zero \" in  New York City  after visiting with police and firefighters there. [47]"}
{"date": 37, "url": 37, "text": "May 6  \u2013 President Obama visits  Fort Campbell  where he meets with members of  SEAL Team Six  who participated in the  raid on Osama bin Laden's compound ; the President also awards  Presidential Unit Citations  to the military units involved in the operation. [48]"}
{"date": 38, "url": 38, "text": "May 10  \u2013 President Obama delivers a speech in  El Paso, Texas , on  immigration reform . [49]"}
{"date": 39, "url": 39, "text": "May 23  \u2013 President Obama begins a state visit to  Ireland . [50]"}
{"date": 40, "url": 40, "text": "May 24  \u2013 President Obama arrives in United Kingdom for a state visit. [51]"}
{"date": 41, "url": 41, "text": "May 26  \u2013 President Obama attends the  G8 summit  in  Deauville, France . [52]"}
{"date": 42, "url": 42, "text": "May 29  \u2013 President Obama visits  Joplin, Missouri , in response to the city's  recent tornado destruction . [53]"}
{"date": 43, "url": 43, "text": "June 3  \u2013 President Obama travels to  Toledo, Ohio , and delivers remarks to workers at the  Chrysler Group  Toledo Supplier Park. [54]"}
{"date": 44, "url": 44, "text": "June 7  \u2013 The President welcomes German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  to the White House for a state visit. [55]"}
{"date": 45, "url": 45, "text": "June 14  \u2013 President Obama visits  Puerto Rico , the first such trip by a sitting U.S. President since  John F. Kennedy . [56]"}
{"date": 46, "url": 46, "text": "June 18  \u2013 President Obama teams up with  Speaker of the House   John Boehner  in a round of  golf  against Vice President Biden and Ohio Governor  John Kasich . [57]"}
{"date": 47, "url": 47, "text": "June 22  \u2013 The President announces his plan to withdraw 33,000 U.S. troops from  Afghanistan  by the summer of 2012. [58]"}
{"date": 48, "url": 48, "text": "July 10\u201314  \u2013 The President holds a series of daily meetings with  Congressional  leaders at the White House in an attempt to reach an agreement on raising the  debt ceiling . [59]"}
{"date": 49, "url": 49, "text": "July 24  \u2013 President Obama calls  House Minority Leader   Nancy Pelosi  and  Senate Majority Leader   Harry Reid  to the White House for an update on negotiations concerning the  ongoing debt ceiling impasse . [60]"}
{"date": 50, "url": 50, "text": "July 25  \u2013 The President delivers a  prime time  television address about the debt ceiling debate. [61]"}
{"date": 51, "url": 51, "text": "August 2  \u2013 The President signs into law the  Budget Control Act of 2011 , ( Pub.L. 112\u201325 ,  S. 365 , 125\u00a0 Stat. \u00a0 240 , enacted August\u00a02, 2011), to raise the federal debt ceiling, avoid default, and create a bipartisan \"super committee\" to deliberate on debt reductions. [62]"}
{"date": 52, "url": 52, "text": "August 9  \u2013 President Obama\u2014accompanied by high-ranking military officials and Secretary of Defense  Leon Panetta \u2014travels to  Dover Air Force Base  to pay his respects to troops killed when  their helicopter was downed in Afghanistan . [63]"}
{"date": 53, "url": 53, "text": "August 15\u201317  \u2013 President Obama embarks on a three-day, five-city bus tour to host town hall meetings to discuss the economy and jobs. On August 15, the President stopped in  Cannon Falls, Minnesota , and  Decorah, Iowa . The President is scheduled to make stops in  Peosta, Iowa , on August 16 and in  Atkinson, Illinois , and  Alpha, Illinois , on August 17. [64]"}
{"date": 54, "url": 54, "text": "August 18  \u2013 President Obama calls for Syrian President  Bashar al-Assad  to step down and issues an  executive order  prohibiting certain financial transactions with  Syria . [65]"}
{"date": 55, "url": 55, "text": "August 26\u201327  \u2013 President Obama returns a day early to  Washington, D.C. , from his vacation on  Martha's Vineyard  ahead of  Hurricane Irene . [66]  In response to the hurricane, the President declares a  state of emergency  for  Connecticut ,  Massachusetts ,  New Hampshire ,  New Jersey ,  New York , and  Virginia . [67]"}
{"date": 56, "url": 56, "text": "September 8  \u2013 In  a speech delivered to a joint session of Congress , President Obama presents the  American Jobs Act , his plan to create jobs and revive the economy. [68]"}
{"date": 57, "url": 57, "text": "September 12  \u2013 The President delivers a speech in the  White House Rose Garden  to promote his American Jobs Act. [69]"}
{"date": 58, "url": 58, "text": "September 16  \u2013 President Obama signs the  America Invents Act , ( H.R. 1249 ), a major overhaul of the U.S. patent system, into law. [70]"}
{"date": 59, "url": 59, "text": "September 19  \u2013 The President releases his debt reduction plan and the  Buffett Rule . [71]"}
{"date": 60, "url": 60, "text": "October 6  \u2013 The President, speaking at a press conference from the White House, urges the Senate to pass his  American Jobs Act . [72]"}
{"date": 61, "url": 61, "text": "October 11  \u2013 The President asks Harry Reid to hold votes on separate parts of his  American Jobs Act  after it fails to secure a filibuster-proof supermajority in the Senate. [73]"}
{"date": 62, "url": 62, "text": "October 13  \u2013 The President and First Lady host their fifth  state dinner  at the White House to honor South Korean President  Lee Myung-bak . [74]"}
{"date": 63, "url": 63, "text": "October 14  \u2013 In a letter to Congress, President Obama announces that he has authorized the deployment of \"about 100\" U.S. troops to  Africa  \"to provide assistance to regional forces that are working toward the removal of  Joseph Kony \" (leader of the  Lord's Resistance Army ). [75]"}
{"date": 64, "url": 64, "text": "October 16  \u2013 The President speaks at the dedication ceremony for the  Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial  in Washington, D.C. [76]"}
{"date": 65, "url": 65, "text": "October 17\u201319  \u2013 President Obama makes a three-day bus tour of North Carolina and Virginia to promote his  jobs plan . [77]"}
{"date": 66, "url": 66, "text": "October 20  \u2013 Speaking from the  White House Rose Garden , the President delivers remarks on the  death of Muammar Gaddafi . [78]"}
{"date": 67, "url": 67, "text": "October 21  \u2013 The President announces that by the end of the year nearly all U.S. troops in  Iraq  will be withdrawn and the  Iraq War  will be over. [79]"}
{"date": 68, "url": 68, "text": "November 3  \u2013 President Obama attends the  G-20 summit  in  Cannes, France . [80]"}
{"date": 69, "url": 69, "text": "November 11  \u2013 The President places a wreath on the  Tomb of the Unknowns  and speaks at  Arlington National Cemetery  in honor of  Veterans Day . [81]  Later in the day, the President and First Lady attend the first annual  Carrier Classic  aboard the  USS  Carl Vinson  in  San Diego . [82]"}
{"date": 70, "url": 70, "text": "November 12\u201319  \u2013 The President attends the  APEC economic summit  in  Honolulu  (November 12\u201315) before traveling to  Australia  and  Bali, Indonesia . [83]"}
{"date": 71, "url": 71, "text": "November 18  \u2013 While visiting Bali, Indonesia, President Obama announces Hillary Clinton's plan to visit  Burma , the first by a Secretary of State in more than 50 years. [84]"}
{"date": 72, "url": 72, "text": "November 23  \u2013 President Obama officially pardons two  turkeys , \"Liberty\" and \"Peace\", during the  National Thanksgiving Turkey Presentation . [85]"}
{"date": 73, "url": 73, "text": "November 28  \u2013 President Obama hosts a White House summit for leaders of the  European Union  to discuss the  European sovereign debt crisis . [86]"}
